Thanks for filing this — the request is clear and well-motivated.

The fix is in `SKNativeObject` (the base class for all SkiaSharp objects), line 242 of `binding/SkiaSharp/SKObject.cs`:

```csharp
// Current
protected internal bool IsDisposed => isDisposed == 1;

// Proposed
public bool IsDisposed => isDisposed == 1;
```

This is a single-line, ABI-safe change that immediately exposes `IsDisposed` on `SKBitmap`, `SKPath`, `SKCanvas`, and every other SkiaSharp object.

> **Note on thread safety:** As mentioned in comments above, `IsDisposed` is a point-in-time check. Another thread could dispose the object after you read `false`, so callers still need their own synchronization if shared ownership is involved. However, this is no different from `IDisposable` patterns elsewhere in .NET — exposing the property is the right call.

This will be tracked as a small enhancement for an upcoming release.
